issuesFound.explanation:
`inlineValidator._renderResult()` only adds CSS classes; it never adds or removes the `aria-invalid` attribute, so validation errors are invisible to assistive technology.  
Fix (replace the body of `_renderResult` with):  
```javascript
if (result.valid) {
  setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'false');
  removeClass(field, CSS.fieldInvalid);
  addClass(field, CSS.fieldValid);
} else {
  setAttr(field, 'aria-invalid', 'true');
  addClass(field, CSS.fieldInvalid);
  removeClass(field, CSS.fieldValid);
}
errorEl.textContent = result.firstError;
```

